The goal of Tanzania PEPFAR funding is to initiate a data revolution to achieve greater transparency, mutual accountability and local impact in Sub-Saharan Africa.  The program will seek to attempt to address some of the root causes of insufficient data use for decision-making around HIV/AIDS, broader health, gender equality, and economic growth.

The goal of Cote d'Ivoire PEPFAR funding is to initiate a data revolution to achieve greater transparency, mutual accountability and local impact in Sub-Saharan Africa.  The program will seek to attempt to address some of the root causes of insufficient data use for decision-making around HIV/AIDS, broader health, gender equality, and economic growth.

MCC is authorized under section 614(g) of its legislation to contract with any nongovernmental organization (including a university, independent foundation, or other organization) in the United States or in Honduras that is undertaking research aimed at improving data related to eligibility criteria with respect to the country.

MCC is authorized under section 614(g) of its legislation to contract with any nongovernmental organization (including a university, independent foundation, or other organization) in the United States or in a candidate country that is undertaking research aimed at improving data related to eligibility criteria with respect to the country.

Category of MCC funds used for the purposes of covering the costs associated with MCC's daily operations. These include, but are not limited to, salaries and benefits, travel, rent, information technology, overseas operations and contracted services.

Compact Development funding (CDF) is used pre-compact for key project preparation work such as feasibility and environmental impact studies, engineering designs, baseline surveys, financial management and procurement technical assistance, and other specialized analysis to help MCC determine the final suitability and scope of investments, costs, implementation risks, and mitigation measures.
A Threshold Program agreement is a contract between the United States and an eligible country through which MCC provides financial assistance for targeted policy reform efforts.

Due diligence funding is used to obtain sufficient information to evaluate, assess and appraise projects during compact development, effectively oversee and monitor compact implementation, conduct quality assurance, and then evaluate the results of a compact project once complete.

MCC is authorized under section 614(g) of its legislation to contract with any nongovernmental organization (including a university, independent foundation, or other organization) in the United States or in El Salvador that is undertaking research aimed at improving data related to eligibility criteria with respect to the country.
